caption: Best pizza around!!
Our favorite pizza in Roswell
Love ZuZZu! Friendly staff. Great service. Relaxed atmosphere. Any wonderful food.
The food is really authentic and service was great.
Everything is good here. Fresh, service is great. A nice homey feel. So worth the time to go here.

Zuzzu is the best authentic Sicilian food in Atlanta! The service is fantastic and the atmosphere is cozy. I really appreciate the lengths that ownership has taken to be sure that all employees are masked, hand sanitizer is available, the seating is spread out and that all customers feel comfortable.
THE BEST. SERVICE OUTSTANDING,KITCHEN HUMMS WITH AUTHENTICITY,THE CHEF GIUSEPPE BLENDS FINEST INGREDIENTS, LOVE&KNOWLEDGE OF SICILY,WINE&BEER SELECTION FANTASTIC.CALL,MAKE A RES,JUST ENJOY
Absolutely loved the food and the quaintness of the restaurant. Our server, Alex, was fantastic! We will definitely be back to try some more entrees and pizzas!
Eating our way around the menu and so far everything has been fantastic. Pizzas are the best in Roswell, the guys who work there are great and have even "gone off-menu" on request. Awesome place.
Hidden gem in Roswell!! Pizza- delish!! Service- top notch and very personal— atmosphere— so great!! Pasta — amazing!! Wine list— off the chart!!

It's a little basic when you enter - but the food and service totally make it a great experience! Between the two of us, we had the meatballs, lasagna, cannoli and tiramisu. Everything was excellent! Loved the fresh bread!
Always a wonderful meal. Super friendly wait staff and of course- delicious food!
Wonderful spot all around. Great service and wonderful food. We got the white pizza with mushrooms/truffle oil and penne alla vodka, and we’d highly recommend both! Already can’t wait to return.
Is awesome!!!

First time customer. Ordered pizza & wow. Pizza was great. I was pleasantly surprised at how good it was. I ordered the Genova Pizza (white pizza & basil pesto). Dude... *applauds* That's what I'm talking about. It is an expensive pizza, similar to mellow mushroom prices, but I am tempted to order the same pizza the very next day. The dough was *italian hand gesture* and the cheese, my gosh *whips & nae naes*.  Thats one tasty pizza ZuZZu.
Margherita and funghi pizzas, halloumi salad and deviled eggs were delicious. We'll be back.
Excellent as usual.
Great service and better wine list. Pizza and pasta dishes also great.
Best pizza I've had in a long time!
We loved it! Calamari and artichoke appetizer and eggplant parmigiana were excellent!
Simply incredible.  Intimate atmosphere with a homestyle vibe.   Awesome food and service.
Fresh ingredients and excellent service. Super yummy food.
Great food,  stylish decor,  friendly service.
Perfect restaurant and wonderful employees. Thanjs for everything....
Great food, great service!
Everything was amazing, food, service, and great environment! Your Neighborhood super spot!
Great Freaking Food and Service.
Incredible experience & the food is phenomenal!  I had the eggplant Parmesan which was top notch. Highly recommend!
Food was great and staff was really friendly

Absolutely delicious and the best service you could ever ask for. This place, is home away from home. Instant family!! Will be back 1,000x's. Thank you for the wonderful Christmas Eve service!❤ Happy New Year to my favorite restaurant!!
Great hidden gem in Roswell. The lasagna, the pizzas, the chicken parm or the house made pasta are all fantastic. You won't ve disappointed!
Amazing food fast! Great prices! Great atmosphere and people!

Zuzzu's consistently delivers great food and attentive service. They have a new grilled Halloumi cheese salad which is fantastic; great combination of flavors while still being light. The owner, Sam, will always make sure your experience is good.
Good food. Friendly service. Slow.

It's one of the few restaurant that really gets close to the Italian tastes and recipes. The pizza is really special, and the meatballs are great. Though, the restaurant serves food of different southern Italian regions, like the typical Neapolitan wood-fired pizza, and the eggplant parmigiana. Even though not really just Sicilian, the food is superb!! The service is good as well, and the owner is involved in caring after every table, making sure every guest had the best experience. Plus, the wine list is very special, they serve some Italian wines that are very rare to find on USA! Only downside, eggplant parmesan a little too oily, and carpaccio heavy on the lemon. Overall, great experience!
Very nice atmosphere. Great menu.  Fantastic service.  Food was delightful and interesting. Even the salad was great!
Pizza was soggy and had black spots on bottom from wood oven. The pizza didn't taste good and Coke cans are sold for $3.50 at ZuZZu; a complete ripoff.
Really good food and nice, friendly staff.  Recommended!

(Translated by Google) I never thought of getting in the city of Atlanta a restaurant of this gastronomic category, gourmet Italian food, an attention that makes you feel as if you were at home, all at affordable prices. 100% recommendable  (Original) Jamas pensé conseguir en la ciudad de Atlanta un restaurant de esta categoria gastronomica, comida italiana gourmet, una atención que te hace sentir como si estuvieras en casa, todo a precios asequibles. 100% recomendable
Fantastic little Italian place in Roswell. You're going to pay for it, but at least you're going to enjoy it. Most everything is homemade so quantities can be limited.
Lovely little place. Amazing food! Pizza is incredible.  And the salted caramel gelato,  oh my! Lovely staff and ambience.  Go, you will be glad you did.
Truly delicious food and friendly staff. A bit noisy though.

Absolutely one of the best dining experiences in many years! The food was mouth wateringly prepared to perfection, and the service was above expectations. 3 entrees and a salad for 60 dollars plus tax and tip, but we also enjoyed wine, cannoli and cappuccino. Can't be beat!

Three of us came here for my father's birthday. We split four dishes: Insalata di Burrata, Etna pizza, Saporita (pasta), and Baccala' (cod). Biggest problem was picking which was our favorite. They were all that great. Service was perfect. Look at the pictures and then try it yourself.

Awesome people and they're so passionate about sharing their food with us. We had Insalate Halloumi for salad with heirloom tomatoes, grilled Greek cheese (tastes like meat and with texture). Bistecca Salmoriglio, which is hanger steak (marinated right, and cooked to perfection at medium-rare) ... Oh, go good. We also was being lame with Alfredo Pasta, but that was so good, creamy and comforting!
Great service and great food!
Great atmosphere and food.
Great as usual.
Best pizza Ive ever tasted!!  im sure all food is incredible
Excellent food and wonderful staff!

Excellent spot in the heart of Roswell! Was recommended to me and I’ll recommend it to you all. Excellent customer service, food was delicious, portioned properly, and as fresh as it gets! Good times! Go check them out!
Everything was so good!! We really recommend the  pasta with the ragu sauce as it’s meaty and delicious!  We will add this to one of our regular Roswell dinning options!!

Hands down best pizza in north metro Atlanta - ties with Antico on taste. The cozy atmosphere of Zuzzu, the relationships you can build with the owner and wait staff, and the fact that all of the food superb make this my favorite place to eat!
Uncaring service in all phases.

The food was easily the best italian food that i have ever had in my life. We both ordered the specials that were available for the day. There were 5 of them on the day we visited.  It is a very small restaurant maybe 12 tables total with over half of the tables showing as reserved on the friday night we visited. The wait staff was on their phones when not helping customers out in the open bar area. Some may find this distracting but the wait staff was prompt to bring dishes, refills and catered to all of our reasonable requests quickly. The place could get a bit loud on a night where the tables are all filled i feel like.  The location is out of the way for thos familiar with downtown roswell. However eating here provides the benefit of not paying to park or not having ample parking. There are some spots directly in fromnt of the restaurant or a large lot accross a not so busy street. There is also a beer bar and whiskey bar for after dinner libations within walking distance.  All in all for the price this restaurant far exceeded our expectations and we will be frequenting this restaurant in the future.
One of the better Italian/Sicilian spots OTP Atlanta. Start with the pizza!
Pizzas are AMAZING!
Always great food🍎🍷🍆
Great little place in downtown Roswell with some really good pizza. I will try some of the other dishes on the next trip.
Great food. Fun staff definitely a hidden gem in roswell.
Pizza not good but everything else love it
Beautiful small restaurant with delicious food. Visit this place when you have time to hang out n enjoy the food.

Authentic Sicilian. Great food. Seating is limited so you might want to make a reservation if you are going on a Friday or Saturday night. Have the filet in the lemon caper sauce. It is heaven on Earth.

Delicious and authentic Italian fare just outside of downtown Roswell. Tucked away in a shopping center off the main strip, this delightful little restaurant is filled with charm and lots of homemade delights. We had the specials that night which was eggplant parmesan lasagna and a delicious seafood pasta. Everything was very tasty especially the lasagna although the serving size was a bit small considering the price (very expensive btw!). The service is delightful and all the employees are very friendly. I highly recommend that you reserve though because the seating is very limited and if you don't have a reservation then you may feel a bit like a second class citizen. Also the beer list was outdated and they did not have any of the imports listed. All said I highly recommend this location if you have a hankering for something that'll make you say, mama mia!
Wonderful food and excellent service! Meatball appetizer was delicious!
Pretty good food. A little overpriced. Very nice people running the restaurant.
Great food and atmosphere. Good wine selection.
First time there, incredible! Our server Alex was excellent,  and the food was equally amazing! Highly recommend this restaurant to anyone who enjoys fresh Italian food!!! Will definitely be back!
Food was good. Didn't find the service to be the warmest I've ever been around. Would possibly go back. Loved the bread and freshness of everything though!

The daily specials were fabulous!!! The suggestions for wine were perfect! Sam the owner is quite but very nice and attentive. James is fun and outgoing and makes a mean cappuccino! The fresh bread and ingredients well worth  the price!  Do yourself a favor  and book a reservation a few days in advance  for Friday or Saturday night as it is a small venue.  We got there just as they opened and got two spots at the bar which was fine for us..  The reason we went was we had their pizza before and it was great as well..
Very nice food

Came here without expectations, and surprisingly the food and service were great! We had ordered the eggplant parmigiano, the broccoli side, and the mozzarella pizza (and the house Merlot), and everything was made to order and was good. My very minor complaint is that the restroom was in view of the seating section and didn't have functioning locks on the door, so I would appreciate if there was a screen or curtain between the glass door to the restroom area and the main seating area, and if the locks were fixed. 5 stars overall for the great food, and we will be back here again!

Wow this small cozy Italian spot in the heart of downtown Roswell is phenomenal to say the least.  The owner Sam takes real pride in the menu offered- made to order you can so enjoy! I will continue to frequent this trattoria- it so reminds me of dining out in Italy!
Small place with shortage of parking spaces... everything else - very good. Good food, friendly service. Recommended.
Great food!!

A real surprise, both for location, food and atmosphere.  On a side street in a retail block.  Real Italian food, prepared fresh every day.  Old fashioned pizza oven turns dough into a wonderful crust. Wonderful Italian wines (including the house).  Stay all evening and enjoy the ambience of a long Italian dinner.  A go-to spot for us!
Loved the food... freshness of the pasta lightness of the pizza base..great warm experience
Service needs help, food was mediocre. Will not give it another shot...very disappointed.
Stopped by for lunch and so glad we did! The food and service exceeded my expectations.
Pizza and octopus appetizer were great. We will be going bacj
Such a welcoming owner. The service was excellent and the pie was good. Thanks!

Second visit: Pizza was decent and priced relative to other similar brick oven baked pie places. The homemade sangria was very good. This time bread being cut by someone using a cloth to hold. Only negative was wildly over priced Mediteranian salad at $12 for what would normally be considered a side salad.  Firtst visit:First the good. Very good food and portions making ZuZZu a good value. Nice touches like perfectly baked fresh bread, excellent San Marzano tomato sauce, and house made mozzarella cheese. Chicken parm was excellent and huge. My one and only negative is hygiene. Staff who are bussing tables, handling money, and stroking their beards should not be cutting and plating fresh bread with bear hands. Bread should be held with one side of a clean towel and picked up with tongs. That said, we'll be back :)
What a wonderful experience...the food was fabulous and the service was amazing. A special call-out to Grace, who went above and beyond to make our experience memorable.

I was here with my friend. We ordered two kinds of pasta but it took about an hour. We got there at and ordered food at 8 pm but the food was on the table at 9:05 pm. I just give 2 stars to this review just because of the taste of the Alfredo pasta (which was simple!!!)
We had the special,Mediterranean clams & pasta. Crazy yummy.
Superb wood fired pizza. Great wines.
Very good food and large portions at reasonable prices.
Great food, wine, and people!
Fantastic food
Amazing pizza and a great Italian menu.  Friendly atmosphere.  A great neighborly place that we will love to come back to.  Loved the food.
Great food and a great date night restaurant!
Great Sicilian Food! Chicken Parmesan with Spaghetti was excellent!

Great food. From the homemade bread and olive oil/balsamic mix to the gelato...it's all fantastic. The caprese salad was tasty and well presented. My wife had a pasta dish. The red sauce was delicious. My brother and I had the fungi (mushroom with truffle oil) pizza. We had enough for leftovers. The noise level is a little on the loud side.
Amazing flavor! We ordered two pizzas, they were both delicious! Can't wait to go back!
Everything we ate was delicious! We may have found our new favorite Italian restaurant.
Good restaurant

Ok but not great. I was excited to go back to Zuzzu’s to try their food once again, but left disappointed with the quality and service. I can tell now that they have changed owners it is not what it once was. The place is missing the charisma it had. The food was ok but not great as I tasted it before. There was way too much sauce and it was too salty; it overpowered the flavor completely of the meatballs and mussels in each of the plates we had. Also way to much Parmesan cheese, which I never asked for it, but it already came incredibly loaded with it. If someone would ask me to go back again I will probably pass on it. There are more competitive options around the area.
Personal service, salty, but tasty. Really slow.

If it came down to food alone Zuzzu would get  5 stars. Unfortunately the service was far below par. We waited an hour and 15 minutes to get 3 pizzas and a pasta dish when the restaurant was almost empty. We were also ignored for the most part and never got refills or any attention unless we got someone's attention. I might try it again and will update this post if I do.

Had the opportunity to try this last night and we were not disappointed. The service was impeccable and the food was flavorful and delightful. We would have taken pictures, but time was of the essence...no time to waste on pictures, we had to dig in! The location is great with easy parking, which is hard to come by in Roswell.
Amazing food, staff, and owner. Meatballs were amazeballz, lasagna was delicioso, and wood-fired pizza was perfection. Nice laid back ambiance away from the craze.
Wonderful salads, pizza and lasagna. The beets in the salad were sweet and delicious.
The best eggplant parm ever!! Sammy the owner is awesome!
Awesome food and service in a tucked away location.  Hope it all can stay that way.

Very clean and upbeat contemporary Italian kitchen with fresh ingredients and good tasting food and drink. Welcoming staff and personable owner. Make reservations for Fridays and  Saturdays. Week nights are more flexible.
Great service and food; from the drinks to the bread, from the appetizers to the meals, from the gelato to the mouth. Does it make sense? It doesn't have to. Just go.
Great quality and great service!
Tasty pizza

great experience here Saturday night. Wonderful new owner as of May 2017 (Sam), and lovely staff, (James and Angela). Best meatballs ever in sauce over cheese. Delicious eggplant casserole and chicken parmesan. Salads looked great. Brought home a wonderful white pizza, cooked in front of us in Italian oven. The cannoli, however, with imported Italian baby choc chips was to die for. Can't wait to go back to this darling neighborhood restaurant on Oak ST in Roswell GA. And, it's very reasonable.
Fantastic meal. Wine selection was excellent. Service was attentive. Exceptionally pleased.
Love the food, atmosphere, music and people! Best Italian in the area!
Fabulous food, delectable wine, definitely recommend!
Great neighborhood Italian place.  Cozy, nice but casual atmosphere.
Service and food, marginal at best...Not worth the price of admission....

Fabrizzio made the whole experience a whole different level. Great place, still with the normal nuances of a new place, but the food is espectacular, the bread, the pasta, perfect family joint for people living in the Roswell area. I would love to have a hang out type place like this in my area.
What a great little place! I have tried Italian restaurants all over Metro Atlanta and this is one of the best I've had, hands down. We will be back!
Stopped in for a glass of wine and a sweet snack. The owner was there and was super nice and enthusiastic about his restaurant. Definitely recommend!
LOVE this place.  The owner is so helpful, food is OUT OF THIS WORLD!
A true hidden gem, the owners personally attended to us, the food was amazing, the Gelato was hand made by the owner and simply the best I've ever had, a must see
My wife and I went for lunch and had a wonderful experience
Fabulous home cooked authentic italian. Small place only 8 tablea so it gets filled quickly. But worth it for the food.
Nice new spot in Roswell. Tradition Sicilian food. Great sauce and pizza. Down to earth staff, but wonderful food. Call ahead. The dining area is small.
The food was delicious, great service, and very reasonably priced especially for Roswell.  We will definately be back.
Service is still a little "new restaurant spotty" but quick to recover from any errors.  The food was absolutely wonderful.  The wine fun.  The staff friendly.  We are going back!

Had a wonderful meal there last night. The food was outstanding and the service was also. This is a rare undiscovered new gem in Roswell. If you like authentic Italian food, you will enjoy this wonderful restaurant run by a fine local family. Highly recommend!!
ZuZZu is tops. It's the best place for Italian in the north Atlanta metro that I've tried! They have a wood-burning oven if neapolitan pizza is your thing.
Not only is the food great but the people serving you this amazing meal are wonderful. The staff provides an atmosphere that is personable and genuine!

The pasta was okay.  The pizza was raw on top and burned on the bottom, with perhaps 3 slices of pepperoni.   When we complained, the owner simply shrugged saying "that's how we do it in Sicily.  We ordered a bottle of wine and were told they were out, then suggested another.  We foolishly did not ask the price - he picked a much more expensive bottle. When we got the bill, he charged us for THREE bottles of wine.  When we asked it be corrected, he brought us the bill for the next table.  It was a rather expensive bad experience. This restaurant  won't last long unless they fix their act.

A really hidden gem with great food and a very friendly staff. The owner clearly is passionate about making great food and was happy to even stop by our table and chat for a few minutes. We'll definitely be going back again.
Great pasta, wonderful people, intimate local atmosphere. What more could we ask for! You must give Zuzzu a try. Sal and the staff are so welcoming ... And the food is great!
